    "body": "### Problem\n\nSome plugins, such as [rustaceanvim](https://github.com/mrcjkb/rustaceanvim/tree/4c5fc771694ab09ec618ea2baabaf34420d86edb?tab=readme-ov-file#gear-advanced-configuration), support setting some plugin options via `vim.lsp.config('rust-analyzer', { default_settings = { ... } }`. I'm curious whether adding our own fields is discouraged or not.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nBefore/After for `rustaceanvim`:\n\n```lua\n-- Before\nvim.g.rustaceanvim = vim.tbl_deep_extend(\n  'force', \n  vim.g.rustaceanvim or {}, \n  { server = { default_settings = { ... } } }\n)\n\n-- After\nvim.lsp.config('rust-analyzer', { default_settings = { ... } }\n-- or in lsp/rust-analyzer.lua\nreturn { default_settings = { ... } }\n```\n\nBefore/After for `blink.cmp` (using WIP V2 APIs)\n\n```lua\n-- Before\nlocal cmp = require('blink.cmp')\ncmp.lsp.config('rust-analyzer', { max_items = 10 })\n\n-- After\nvim.lsp.config('rust-analyzer', { blink_cmp = { max_items = 10 } })\n-- or in lsp/rust-analyzer.lua\nreturn { blink_cmp = { max_items = 10 } }\n```\n\nIn both cases, it's still possible to include the LSP specific configuration in `lsp/*.lua` by including the \"Before\" option before the `return`. However, for plugins, you would need to check that blink.cmp exists before configuring. For example:\n\n```lua\nif pcall(require, 'blink.cmp') then\n  local cmp = require('blink.cmp')\n  cmp.lsp.config('rust-analyzer', { max_items = 10 })\nend\n\nreturn {\n -- regular lsp config\n}\n```",
