            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "> Another thing that I thought might be useful as a custom field for `vim.lsp.Config` is something like `install`. This can serve as a central place for \"language packs\" to provide a method for an automated installation of an LSP server.\n\nI have something similar to that. I've written a personal wrapper for `mason.nvim` which adds a custom `mason` field to specify what packages to install. That way I configure and install my language servers in a single place in my dotfiles.\n",
